1 2. A person operating a bicycle [, an electric bicycle or an electric scooter]
2 approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign may proceed cautiously
3 through the intersection without stopping if the person:
4 (a) Ascertains that such movement can be made safely;
5 (b) Decreases the speed of the bicycle [, electric bicycle or electric scooter]
6 and confirms that the intersection is clear before entering the intersection; and
7 (c) Yields the right-of-way to pedestrians and all vehicles whose proximity
8 constitutes an immediate hazard.
9 3. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 4, a person operating a
10 bicycle [, an electric bicycle or an electric scooter] upon a roadway may proceed
11 cautiously through an intersection where the signal is a steady red signal or make
12 a turn through any such intersection if the person:
13 (a) Stops before entering the intersection as required by subsection 1;
14 (b) Ascertains that such movement can be made safely; and
15 (c) Yields the right-of-way to pedestrians and all vehicles whose proximity
16 constitutes an immediate hazard.
17 4. A person operating a bicycle [, an electric bicycle or an electric scooter]
18 upon a roadway shall not turn left through an intersection where the signal is a
19 steady red signal unless the roadway onto which the person is turning is a one-
20 way roadway.
21 Sec. 2. NRS 484B.760 is hereby amended to read as follows:
22 484B.760 1. It is a civil infraction punishable pursuant to NRS 484A.703 to
23 484A.705, inclusive, for any person to do any act forbidden or fail to perform any
24 act required in NRS 484B.768 to 484B.790, inclusive [.] , and section 1 of this act.
25 2. The parent of any child and the guardian of any ward shall not authorize or
26 knowingly permit the child or ward to violate any of the provisions of chapters
27 484A to 484E, inclusive, of NRS.
28 3. The provisions applicable to bicycles, electric bicycles and electric scooters
29 apply whenever a bicycle, an electric bicycle or an electric scooter is operated upon
30 any highway or upon any path set aside for the exclusive use of bicycles, electric
31 bicycles and electric scooters subject to those exceptions stated herein.
32 Sec. 3. NRS 484B.763 is hereby amended to read as follows:
33 484B.763 Every person riding a bicycle, an electric bicycle or an electric
34 scooter upon a roadway has all of the rights and is subject to all of the duties
35 applicable to the driver of a vehicle except as otherwise provided in NRS 484B.767
36 to 484B.790, inclusive, and section 1 of this act, and except as to those provisions
37 of chapters 484A to 484E, inclusive, of NRS which by their nature can have no
38 application.

